    <div class="orn"><span class="d"></span></div>
    <h2 id="faq">Questions Women Ask Before They Start</h2>
  </div>

  <h3>Do I need to show my face to create content?</h3>
  <p>No. Most faceless brands get this wrong by removing people entirely, which leaves nothing to recognize. The stronger move is a consistent AI persona who becomes your brand's face — she appears everywhere, and she isn't you.</p>

  <h3>How often should I post?</h3>
  <p>Less often than you think, more consistently than you're managing. A sustainable rhythm you can hold for a year beats a heroic month followed by silence.</p>

  <h3>Is AI-written content bad for SEO?</h3>
  <p>Unhelpful content is bad for SEO regardless of how it was made. AI-assisted content that's genuinely useful is fine. Thin content was always thin.</p>

  <h3>What if I'm not good at design?</h3>
  <p>Design stops being a skill problem once it's a template problem. Five layouts you reuse forever require taste once, not weekly.</p>

  <h3>Do I need Canva Pro?</h3>
  <p>Not to start. The free plan does templates, uploads, and scheduling-ready exports. Brand Kit and Bulk Create are Pro features, and both save real time once you're producing weekly — but they're an efficiency purchase, not an entry requirement.</p>

  <h3>How do I know what's working?</h3>
  <p>Once a month, find the three pieces that earned the most attention and ask what they share. Make more of that. Ignore everything else at this stage.</p>

